<dl id="n12019b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12019b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12019b"> 19(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Adolphe Frank Kabbala</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Dans son beau livre sur <mark>la Kabbale</mark> (2e &eacute;dition, 1889), <mark>M. Adolphe Frank</mark> affirme et d&eacute;montre l&apos;existence, chez les juifs, d&apos;une doctrine secr&egrave;te et d&apos;une tradition orale ind&eacute;pendante de leur tradition &eacute;crite, qui s&apos;est conserv&eacute;e jusqu&apos;au moyen &acirc;ge et fut r&eacute;dig&eacute;e alors dans le livre de Zohar et du S&eacute;pher Jetzirah. M. Franck <font color="green">[sic]</font> trouve l&apos;origine de cette doctrine dans celle des mages persans. <br><font color="green">[In his fine book on the Kabbala (2nd edition, 1889), M . Adolphe Frank affirms and demonstrates the existence, among the jews, of a secret doctrine and an oral tradition that is independent of the written one, which has been conserved until the Middle Ages and then written down in the book of Zohar and of S&eacute;pher Jetzirah. M. Franck finds the origin of this doctrine among the Persian magi.]</font> <small> &Eacute;douard Schur&eacute;, <a name="ESLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ESLL"><cite title="source">Les Grandes L&eacute;gendes de France</cite></a> (1892) 164n</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: A reference to Adolphe Franck, <cite>la Kabbale</cite>, 3. &eacute;d. (Paris: Hachette, 1892). VI.C.15b transcription ends here.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c12bfrg" href="c12all.htm#c12bfrg">VI.C.12:bfr(g)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
